 LINUS CHUBUIKE A former Chairman of Dekina Local Government Area in Kogi State, Adejo Akowe, is dead. Akowe died four days after he was shot by suspected assassins around Ayingba. The former council boss died on Saturday morning at the National Hospital, Abuja where he was being treated. Recall that he had survived a gunshot during the last kogi State governorship election. He was a staff of the Kogi State Sport Council before joining politics. Burial arrangements will be announced soon, according to family sources. 